<h2>HVAC Systems for Meridian</h2>

<p>Meridian's cold-dry climate demands HVAC systems capable of efficient heating during harsh winters and effective cooling during hot, dry summers. Heat pumps are increasingly popular as they provide both heating and cooling efficiently, with cold-climate heat pumps performing well even in sub-zero temperatures. For traditional systems, gas furnaces with SEER ratings of 16-18 for air conditioning provide excellent efficiency. The dry climate means evaporative cooling can be effective as a supplemental cooling method, reducing overall energy consumption.</p>

